01:13:41.990 --> 01:13:44.840
And I came by and some
guys approached me

01:13:44.840 --> 01:13:46.570
and said, "Don't worry about her.

01:13:46.570 --> 01:13:48.390
These people, this is a trick.

01:13:48.390 --> 01:13:49.690
Don't give her money."

01:13:49.690 --> 01:13:51.240
And I thought it's fascinating

01:13:51.240 --> 01:13:55.150
that these kids learn
tricks to get more money.

01:13:55.150 --> 01:13:57.980
She was making noise
so that she's crying

01:13:57.980 --> 01:14:02.660
and maybe people will pay her
more money, and then as we left,

01:14:02.660 --> 01:14:04.770
she got up and she was
walking and then we turned

01:14:04.770 --> 01:14:06.560
around again, and I called her.

01:14:06.560 --> 01:14:07.860
I said, "What are you doing here?"

01:14:07.860 --> 01:14:11.970
And she said, "I'm
collecting [inaudible]."

01:14:11.970 --> 01:14:13.630
I asked her how old you are?

01:14:13.630 --> 01:14:14.930
She's nine years old.

01:14:14.930 --> 01:14:20.800
She looked -- her skin looked like
she's at least 40, and she said --

01:14:20.800 --> 01:14:23.060
I said, "How come you're
collecting [inaudible] here?"

01:14:23.060 --> 01:14:27.410
And she said, "Well my father was
killed in the last bombing of U.S.,

01:14:27.410 --> 01:14:30.920
and I've been doing
this for two months now

01:14:30.920 --> 01:14:35.200
because I have a small brother,
and there's no job for my mother."

01:14:35.200 --> 01:14:37.500
I give her a bunch of money, and
I said, "Let's go to your house.

01:14:37.500 --> 01:14:38.800
Can I visit your Mom?"

01:14:38.800 --> 01:14:41.930
She said, "No, I don't want to go
home because my mother will be mad

01:14:41.930 --> 01:14:45.710
at me because I come home early."

01:14:45.710 --> 01:14:49.340
So most of the children are
either begging out on the streets

01:14:49.340 --> 01:14:55.520 position:56%
or working to earn about $2 to $3 a
day to survive for the whole family,

01:14:55.520 --> 01:14:57.500
and they don't have much to
eat at the end of the day.

01:14:57.500 --> 01:15:03.180
They just eat bread and tea and
maybe sugar if they have it.

01:15:03.180 --> 01:15:06.060
But these kids are very happy.

01:15:06.060 --> 01:15:10.740
I mean, this is what surprises me
that they just have such a spirit.

01:15:10.740 --> 01:15:14.250
This is our computer
center in Kabul.

01:15:14.250 --> 01:15:15.850
Unfortunately, I don't
have a better slide.

01:15:15.850 --> 01:15:20.090
If you go to our site,
www.afghanistan [inaudible].com,

01:15:20.090 --> 01:15:24.390
you'll see other pictures of
the organization and our work

01:15:24.390 --> 01:15:27.790
and this is a computer
center that we have in Kabul.

01:15:27.790 --> 01:15:30.550
We have many students.

01:15:30.550 --> 01:15:33.190
It's actually filled up.

01:15:33.190 --> 01:15:36.170
It's -- what keeps us working
and going is the spirit

01:15:36.170 --> 01:15:39.410
of the Afghan people and the
commitment and the passion

01:15:39.410 --> 01:15:44.530
that the kids have for
learning and knowledge

01:15:44.530 --> 01:15:49.760
and it really makes me work
more, want to work more.

01:15:49.760 --> 01:15:52.240
I mean, the fact that they came --
it was in the middle of the winter

01:15:52.240 --> 01:15:55.620
in December, and all these kids
were coming to school for --

01:15:55.620 --> 01:15:58.310
we normally don't have schools in
the winter time because it's very,

01:15:58.310 --> 01:16:00.330
very cold, but they were preparing

01:16:00.330 --> 01:16:02.660
for the regular school
year for March.

01:16:02.660 --> 01:16:07.840 position:56%
And these kids came and most schools
had no chairs, nothing on the floors

01:16:07.840 --> 01:16:09.580
and they were sitting
there freezing,

01:16:09.580 --> 01:16:12.500
but schools were filled
up with kids.

01:16:12.500 --> 01:16:13.890
It was amazing.

01:16:13.890 --> 01:16:18.750
How -- where they got all of
that commitment, I have no idea.

01:16:24.140 --> 01:16:26.350
Okay. I'm finished actually.

01:16:26.350 --> 01:16:29.580
I just wanted to tell you a
short story about this orphanage

01:16:29.580 --> 01:16:31.330
that we have in [inaudible] area.

01:16:31.330 --> 01:16:35.510
This is what encourages me
to work in Afghanistan is

01:16:35.510 --> 01:16:39.590
that we have 30 orphans, and when I
asked them this last time two weeks

01:16:39.590 --> 01:16:41.990
ago what do they want
me to bring for them?

01:16:41.990 --> 01:16:44.740
They said satellite dish
because we want to talk

01:16:44.740 --> 01:16:46.040
to you when you're there.

01:16:46.040 --> 01:16:49.440
And we want to know what other
fun things is over there,

01:16:49.440 --> 01:16:52.180
and we want to know
more about there.

01:16:52.180 --> 01:16:55.150
There is like -- they
didn't really know where,

01:16:55.150 --> 01:16:58.730
but they knew that there is
this other place that I go to

01:16:58.730 --> 01:17:00.900
and I come back and other
people go and come back,

01:17:00.900 --> 01:17:02.950
and there are other things
that they just want to know.

01:17:02.950 --> 01:17:06.150 position:56%
And then when I ask them what do
you want to become when you grow up?

01:17:06.150 --> 01:17:09.270 position:56%
This 80-year-old said the president.

01:17:11.240 --> 01:17:16.370
And one very major concern for
me is that there are still areas

01:17:16.370 --> 01:17:20.670
in Afghanistan like
[inaudible] which is an area

01:17:20.670 --> 01:17:24.850
where it's very difficult to get to
and they have not had any schools

01:17:24.850 --> 01:17:28.350
in [inaudible] but a lot

01:17:28.350 --> 01:17:30.170
of [inaudible] have
found shelter there,

01:17:30.170 --> 01:17:31.970
and they have only
[inaudible] schools.

01:17:31.970 --> 01:17:33.970
I was trying to go there this time.

01:17:33.970 --> 01:17:36.460
Unfortunately, there was not
enough time and people thought

01:17:36.460 --> 01:17:39.930
that I shouldn't go
because it's too dangerous,

01:17:39.930 --> 01:17:43.770
and this will may become another
home for the fundamentalists.

01:17:43.770 --> 01:17:45.570
Thank you very much.

